# A debounce function prevents a function from executing multiple times in rapid succession.

```javascript
function debounce(func, delay) {
    let timeoutId;
    return function(...args) {
        const context = this;
        clearTimeout(timeoutId);
        timeoutId = setTimeout(() => {
            func.apply(context, args);
        }, delay);
    };
}

// Example: Debouncing a window resize event handler
const debouncedResizeHandler = debounce(function() {
    console.log("Window resized, doing something...");
}, 300);

window.addEventListener("resize", debouncedResizeHandler);
```

This example will log to the console only after the user stops resizing the window for 300 milliseconds, preventing potentially hundreds of rapid function calls during a continuous resize.
